value.0: A dangerous feline creature lurks in the grass! Whenever there seem to be targets on the move, Spike is quick to jump on them. Any mouse or rat will do. Spike also gets his name for his sudden bursts of wild energy, quite often running around like a lunatic in the evenings.
This fluffy guy just wants a home!

This previously rather relaxed ranger has grown stern as the nearby beastmen have advanced from their caves. Having gotten himself a new studded leather armor, Nathan seems to take his work as a guard for the animal shelther seriously. He is often stationed at the blockade, just in case any beastmen try to break through.
The Warrior's Resolve, made for one purpose, and one purpose alone.  To keep the warrior steady, to remove doubt and panic, so that he may stand and do what he does best, punish his foes.
This shield is made entirely from the wood of an oak tree and further enchanted by druids to bring forth the strength in the wood's grain.
A large shield is effective protection for the adventurer who can afford the added weight and encumbrance.
This blade is ice cold to the touch and thirsts for orc flesh to tear into.  Orcs have reason to fear when this blade is wielded.

Value.value: Don't mess with the blockade, please. We have to make sure these little fellas stay safe here.

value.0: An animal loving woman, Marie tends to the animal shelter's inhabitants with warm passion and heavy physical work.

Value.value: Hello! Have you come to adopt?

value.0: A cheery young woman who cares for the animals and acts as a greeter for those who visit the shelter. She also carries a bow - just in case any beastmen decide to come for lunch.
This magic bow has a bonus to attack. As well, it allows the wielder to add part of his strength modifier to the damage dealt.

Value.value: Hello, there! Welcome! If you're interested in adopting one of our animals, please make an appointment for a meeting. In the meantime, go find your future best friend. *grins* Or just look around.

This net carries an array of incects at varying stages of life. Predominantly you see butterfly chrysalides, and freshly emerged butterflies of many varieties. Despite this lovely scene, there is an undertone of danger, as the bearded dragons kept in the shelter have since discovered the veritable buffet hanging above them. At least they can't jump high enough to get them. But that does little for the unfortunate incects that lose their grips on their net.
